{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to marty-cagan's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-krug",
    "senderColor": "red",
    "target": "@marty-cagan",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "Task breakdown proposal alignment with product priorities",
    "content": "Marty, the coordinator asked us to re-evaluate the task breakdown as a team. I've shared a detailed proposal with Kent (who's facilitating). The short version:\n\n1. I'm proposing we add a **base HTML layout task** before registration. The page shell — header, nav, main, footer, skip link — is shared infrastructure that every feature page needs. Better to build it once as its own task than have registration invent it on the fly.\n\n2. The rest of the order matches your priority list: registration → login/logout → view+add todo → complete → delete → edit.\n\n3. I've bundled US-2 + US-3 (login/logout) together and US-4 + US-5 (view list + add todo) together, same as you had. Makes sense from both a user flow and implementation perspective.\n\n4. I'm advocating that tasks stay organized by user-visible features, not by technical layers. Every task should deliver something the user can see and do.\n\nDoes this align with your product priorities?"
  }
}

{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to carson-gross's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-krug",
    "senderColor": "red",
    "target": "@carson-gross",
    "targetColor": "orange",
    "summary": "Base HTML layout task proposal - HTMX input needed",
    "content": "Carson, we're re-evaluating the task breakdown as a team. I've proposed adding a **base HTML layout task** before we start features. This is the page shell:\n\n- Askama base template with proper landmarks (header, main, footer, nav)\n- Skip link to main content\n- HTMX script tag (your domain!)\n- CSS stylesheet link\n- Page title block for child templates\n- The chrome that every page inherits\n\nFrom a hypermedia perspective, this is where the HTMX foundation lives. The base template sets up the contract that all feature pages extend. I wanted to make sure you're aligned on this being a separate task before registration, and that you have input on what the base template should include for HTMX patterns (hx-boost on the body? any global configuration?).\n\nI've sent my full proposal to Kent. Check in with him if you want the details."
  }
}
